text: Aksana Salauyeva (born 2 July 1999) is a Belarusian road and track cyclist. At the 2019 European Games she set the Belarusian records, in the team pursuit track cycling. She competed at the 2021 UCI Track Cycling World Championships. == References == Category:1999 births Category:Cyclists Category:Living people
